### 3. Test Suite

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775490634086-j9zsz5/tests/routes.test.ts`

**Tests for GET /users:**

The test suite expects pagination functionality with these test cases:

```typescript
describe("GET /users", () => {
  it("should return paginated users with default page and limit", async () => {
    const res = await request(app).get("/users");
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body).toHaveProperty("data");
    expect(res.body).toHaveProperty("pagination");
    expect(res.body.pagination.page).toBe(1);
    expect(res.body.pagination.limit).toBe(10);
    expect(res.body.data.length).toBe(10);
    expect(res.body.pagination.total).toBe(15);
    expect(res.body.pagination.totalPages).toBe(2);
  });

  it("should return second page", async () => {
    const res = await request(app).get("/users?page=2&limit=10");
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body.data.length).toBe(5);
    expect(res.body.pagination.page).toBe(2);
  });

  it("should respect custom limit", async () => {
    const res = await request(app).get("/users?limit=5");
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body.data.length).toBe(5);
    expect(res.body.pagination.totalPages).toBe(3);
  });

  it("should return empty data for out-of-range page", async () => {
    const res = await request(app).get("/users?page=100");
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body.data).toEqual([]);
    expect(res.body.pagination.page).toBe(100);
  });
});
```

**Expected Response Format:**
```json
{
  "data": [/* User objects */],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 15,
    "totalPages": 2
  }
}
```

**Test Configuration:**
- Uses Vitest as test runner
- Uses Supertest for HTTP request testing
- Imports and tests the Express app directly

---

### 4. Additional Endpoint

There's also a **GET /users/:id** endpoint for fetching individual users:

```typescript
router.get("/users/:id", (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  const user = users.find((u) => u.id === id);
  if (!user) {
    res.status(404).json({ error: "User not found" });
    return;
  }
  res.json(user);
});
```

With corresponding tests for single user retrieval and 404 handling.

---

### Key Observation

The tests expect pagination functionality in the GET /users endpoint response, but the current implementation simply returns all users without pagination. This indicates this is a **work-in-progress** where pagination needs to be implemented to match the test expectations.

